lete|[[Lilian Mariita]]|KEN}} || 1:12:04\n|-\n| May 2, 2015\n| align=left|{{flagathlete|[[Elisa Barno]]|KEN}} || 1:02:31\n| align=left|{{flagathlete|[[Sarah Kiptoo]]|KEN}} || 1:13:09\n|-\n| May 7, 2016\n| align=left| {{flagathlete|[[MacDonard Ondara]]|KEN}} || 1:02:03\n| align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Ogla Kimaiyo]]|KEN}} || 1:11:43\n|-\n| May 6, 2017\n| align=left| {{flagathlete|[[John Murugu]]|KEN}} || 1:04:53\n| align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Margaret Maina]]|KEN}} || 1:15:51\n|-\n| May 5, 2018\n| align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Daniel Mesfun]]|ERI}} || 1:03:27\n| align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Dayna Pidhoresky]]|CAN}} || 1:12:47\n|-\n| May 4, 2019\n| align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Panuel Mkungo]]|KEN}} || 1:03:26\n| align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Ivy Kibet]]|KEN}} || 1:12:11\n|-\n|May 2, 2020\n| colspan=\"4\" |Not run due to coronavirus pandemic.\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{sisterlinks|d=Q7092363|c=Category:OneAmerica 500 Festival Mini-Marathon|n=no|b=no|v=no|voy=no|m=no|mw=no|species=no|s=no|wikt=no|q=no}}\n*{{Official website}}\n*\"[http://www.indystar.com/article/20070209/SPORTS14/70129051/Timeline-Indianapolis-Mini-Marathon Timeline of the Indianapolis Mini Marathon]\" at ''[[Indianapolis Star]],'' February 9, 2007\n\n{{Indy 500}}\n\n[[Category:Half marathons in the United States]]\n[[Category:Festivals in Indianapolis]]\n[[Category:Sports competitions in Indianapolis]]\n[[Category:Recurring sporting events established in 1977]]\n[[Category:Annual sporting events in the United States]]\n[[Category:1977 establishments in Indiana]]\n[[Category:Track and field in Indiana]]\n", "name_user": "LilHelpa", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo; mos", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OneAmerica_500_Festival_Mini-Marathon"}
{"title_page": "Money and the Woman", "text_new": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = Money and the Woman\n| image          = \n| alt            = \n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[William K. Howard]]\n| producer       = [[Bryan Foy]]\n| screenplay     = Robert Presnell Sr. \n| story          = [[James M. Cain]]\n| starring       = [[Jeffrey Lynn]]<br>[[Brenda Marshall]]<br>[[John Litel]]<br>[[Lee Patrick (actress)|Lee Patrick]]<br>[[Henry O'Neill]]<br>[[Roger Pryor (actor)|Roger Pryor]]\n| music          = [[Bernhard Kaun]]\n| cinematography = [[L. William O'Connell]] \n| editing        = [[Frank Magee]]\n| studio         = [[Warner Bros.]]\n| distributor    = Warner Bros.\n| released       = {{Film date|1940|8|17}}\n| runtime        = 67 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''Money and the Woman''''' is a 1940 American [[drama film]] directed by [[William K. Howard]] and written by Robert Presnell Sr.. The film stars [[Jeffrey Lynn]], [[Brenda Marshall]], [[John Litel]], [[Lee Patrick (actress)|Lee Patrick]], [[Henry O'Neill]] and [[Roger Pryor (actor)|Roger Pryor]]. The film was released by [[Warner Bros.]] on August 17, 1940.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tcm.com/tcmdb/title/2702/Money-and-the-Woman/ |title=Money and the Woman (1940) - Overview |publisher=TCM.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Crowther |first=Bosley |url=https://www.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9D0CE0D81638E532A25757C0A9669D946193D6CF |title=Movie Review - Diamond Frontier - THE SCREEN IN REVIEW; 'Spring Parade,' a Picture of Life in Old Vienna, With Deanna Durbin as Central Figure at the Roxy-New Films at the Little Carnegie, Rialto and Palace |publisher=NYTimes.com |date=1940-10-04 |accessdate=2015-06-21}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n{{Expand section|date=June 2015}}\n\n== Cast ==\n*[[Jeffrey Lynn]] as Dave Bennett\n*[[Brenda Marshall]] as Barbara Patteson\n